    lines.append(f"- Against the same-cell public pack `{racing_high_c_reference['reference_pack']}`, `racingQuad` capacity is `{fmt(float(racing_high_c_reference['capacity_ratio_preset_over_reference']), 2)}x` and current limit is `{fmt(float(racing_high_c_reference['current_limit_over_reference_continuous']), 2)}x` of the listed continuous-current spec. But if the current preset's `{fmt(float(racing_high_c_lipo['per_cell_ir_mohm']))}` mOhm/cell resistance were used at that reference pack's continuous current, sag would be `{fmt(float(racing_high_c_reference['same_ir_sag_at_reference_current_percent_nominal']), 1)}%` of nominal voltage, so C-rating and ESR must be calibrated separately.")
